I’ve typically been one to stray away from the ‘allow me to reintroduce myself’ posts, however the uptick in new faces on here & new opportunities have called so - here we are! 

You can find me online under the alias of my silly but infamous handle, white trash flash! But personally, you can call me Pamela Anderson (no relation) Just kidding, my name is Sydney. (Yes as in Australia, but any other comparison would be cool) I’m the owner of a beautiful tattoo studio in Calgary, Alberta Canada, but you’ll see me bouncing all over the world. So much so that no one seems to know where I actually live. Whoops! I specialize in Vintage looking tattoos, botanicals and animals…If we can combine all 3, that’s even better! I have been tattooing for 10 years, owning my own shop for nearly 4, and taking my life on the road for the past 6. Im a workaholic and a funaholic, so you’ll usually see me doing at least one of the two. Aside from my career, I love anything country related, motorcycle culture, airplane rides, reading (psychology & philosophy - Favorite book: The Courage to be disliked by ichiro kishimi) healthy eating & lifestyle and above all else, doing hood rat shit with my friends. Random facts: I love politics and playing call of duty. I’m a dog mom of two pocket pitbulls (Bambi & Lambchop) who rule everything around me. Fun fact, my tattoo studio is named after my main bitch bam, because she is Brindle in Color. 

My goal for 2023 is to launch my tooth gem company, lift my truck hehe and start my secondary visa for America. It’s so nice to meet you, and I can’t wait to tattoo ya. Ps if you’re ever feeling nervous or quiet during an appointment just bug me for a story, they are endless. 🗡️🖤
.

Well guys I know this train has sailed but I wanted to lend a minute for the stragglers to catch up on the season. Ink Master, what a wild ride. I used to poke fun at the expression ‘my heart is so full’ but damn there is NO better way to express how this journey has made me feel. Big ups to the boss lady @andreahoak for being more gangster than most, @eric_jon_petho my number one helper, @antcatxx for keeping me in check, our judges which i am honoured to call friends: the 🐐 @djtambe @ryanashleymalarkey @nikkohurtado @joelmadden and all my season 15 family y’all know who you are. (Too many to name) 6th place doesn’t sound nearly as cool as #1 but I am grateful to have even made it that far. Thank you TO ALL who watched & cheered me on, I seen you, I seen you! Without the support I’d surely be locked in a padded room somewhere. So thank you.  Truly, to everyone- thank you. 💕🫶🏻💕
Giddy up

2023 🦋 the obvious major highlight is @inkmaster & the friendships I’ve made along the way. Shoutout to the homies during regular programming on either side of the rollercoaster- you know who you are. Huge things on the horizon for lil ol’ white trashy me - keep your eyes peeled coz 2024 is going to be one for the books! Thanks for everything y’all 💕🎉

🦋
